                  {
                      "id":  "296e647a-32b8-5eb3-bb4c-98bbaf0af29a",
                      "name":  "BQ - CPL Drill",
                      "type":  "n8n-nodes-base.googleBigQuery",
                      "typeVersion":  2,
                      "position":  [
                                       250,
                                       0
                                   ],
                      "credentials":  {
                                          "googleApi":  {
                                                            "id":  "kE5RxM61mQkpV21N",
                                                            "name":  "BigQuery (Qoyod)"
                                                        }
                                      },
                      "parameters":  {
                                         "operation":  "executeQuery",
                                         "projectId":  "angular-axle-492812-q4",
                                         "sqlQuery":  "-- CPL Analysis: mandatory CTE join pattern\n-- Leads source: hubspot_leads_module_daily ONLY (never hubspot_leads_daily = legacy)\n-- Spend source: campaigns_daily (always USD, never SAR)\n-- Pre-aggregate HubSpot before joining to avoid spend fan-out (direct join multiplies spend)\n-- CPL zones (USD): scale \u003c$25 | acceptable $25-$38 | warning $40-$49 | pause \u003e$50\n-- CPQL zones (USD): scale \u003c$85 | acceptable $80-$95 | warning $95-$130 | pause \u003e$160\n-- Entry gate: CPL \u003e $38 USD. Pause: CPL \u003e $50 USD. Scale: CPL \u003c $25 USD.\n-- LinkedIn: campaign GROUP = utm_campaign | Ad Set = utm_audience | Ad = utm_content\n-- Awareness gate (WebsiteTraffic/ImpressionShare/Reach): skip CPL/CPQL checks entirely\n-- 14-day gate: confirm \u003e=14 days data before any pause/scale/budget action\nWITH hs AS (\n  SELECT date, LOWER(lead_utm_campaign) AS campaign_key,\n         SUM(leads_total) AS leads_total,\n         SUM(leads_qualified) AS leads_qualified\n  FROM `angular-axle-492812-q4.qoyod_marketing.hubspot_leads_module_daily`\n  WHERE date \u003e= DATE_SUB(CURRENT_DATE(\u0027Asia/Riyadh\u0027), INTERVAL 30 DAY)\n  GROUP BY date, LOWER(lead_utm_campaign)\n)\nSELECT c.channel, c.campaign_name, c.campaign_id,\n       SUM(c.spend) AS spend,\n       SUM(hs.leads_total) AS leads_total,\n       SUM(hs.leads_qualified) AS leads_qualified,\n       ROUND(SAFE_DIVIDE(SUM(c.spend), SUM(hs.leads_total)), 2) AS cpl,\n       ROUND(SAFE_DIVIDE(SUM(c.spend), SUM(hs.leads_qualified)), 2) AS cpql,\n       ROUND(SAFE_DIVIDE(SUM(hs.leads_qualified), NULLIF(SUM(hs.leads_total),0))*100, 1) AS qual_pct\nFROM `angular-axle-492812-q4.qoyod_marketing.campaigns_daily` c\nLEFT JOIN hs ON c.date = hs.date\n           AND LOWER(c.campaign_name) = hs.campaign_key\nWHERE c.date \u003e= DATE_SUB(CURRENT_DATE(\u0027Asia/Riyadh\u0027), INTERVAL 30 DAY)\n  AND c.channel = \u0027={{$input.first().json.channel}}\u0027\n  AND c.spend \u003e 0\nGROUP BY c.channel, c.campaign_name, c.campaign_id\nHAVING SUM(c.spend) \u003e 0\nORDER BY cpl DESC\nLIMIT 20",
                                         "authentication":  "serviceAccount",
                                         "options":  {

                                                     }
                                     }
                  },
                  {
                      "id":  "fc5340da-e8a1-5747-83ba-e918ddf81711",
                      "name":  "Build Claude Prompt",
                      "type":  "n8n-nodes-base.code",
                      "typeVersion":  2,
                      "position":  [
                                       500,
                                       0
                                   ],
                      "parameters":  {
                                         "mode":  "runOnceForAllItems",
                                         "jsCode":  "const rows=$input.all().map(i=\u003ei.json);\nconst ch=$(\u0027Trigger\u0027).first().json.channel, cpl=$(\u0027Trigger\u0027).first().json.cpl;\n// CPL entry gate: CPL \u003e $38 USD (top of acceptable range). Was wrongly \"$20 SAR\".\n// Filter for rows above acceptable range ($38) for analysis focus\nconst worst=rows.filter(r=\u003e(r.cpl||0)\u003e38).slice(0,8);\nreturn [{json:{\n  system:`You are a paid media analyst for Qoyod (a SaaS company in Saudi Arabia).\n\nCRITICAL KPI RULES:\n- CPL zones (USD): scale \u003c$25 | acceptable $25-$38 | warning $40-$49 | pause \u003e$50\n- CPQL zones (USD): scale \u003c$85 | acceptable $80-$95 | warning $95-$130 | pause \u003e$160\n- CPL entry gate: CPL \u003e $38 USD triggers analysis. Pause threshold: CPL \u003e $50 USD.\n- CPL = SUM(campaigns_daily.spend) / SUM(hubspot_leads_module_daily.leads_total) via CTE join\n- NEVER use channel-reported lead counts. Always use HubSpot lead module data.\n- Spend is always USD. Deal amounts in BQ are already USD. NEVER divide by 3.75.\n- Awareness campaigns (WebsiteTraffic / ImpressionShare / Reach): skip CPL/CPQL checks entirely.\n- 14-day minimum window before any pause/scale/budget action.\n\nLINKEDIN SPECIAL RULE:\n- LinkedIn campaign level: join on utm_campaign (= Campaign Group in LinkedIn UI)\n- LinkedIn ad set level: join on utm_audience (= Campaign in LinkedIn UI)\n- LinkedIn ad level: join on utm_content (= Ad in LinkedIn UI)\n\n\nKEYWORD PAUSE RULES (QS-based, not CPL-based):\n- Pause if: QS \u003c 5 AND \u003e80% lost impression share\n- Converting keyword exception: if QS \u003c 5 AND conv \u003e 4 AND $10 \u003c= CPA \u003c= $70 -\u003e LEAVE ENABLED (keyword is converting despite low QS)\n- Minimum 10-day keyword age before any pause - keywords younger than 10 days: add to monitoring list, no action\n- Zero-active-keyword guard: NEVER pause the last enabled keyword in an ad group (would kill campaign silently)\n- NEVER delete a keyword - only pause\n- QS = 0 (PMax keywords or not-yet-set): skip, cannot evaluate\nAPPROVAL RULE:\n- ALL actions (pause, scale, bid change, budget shift) must queue to #approvals channel\n- Execution only after emoji reaction from approver\n- Exception: bid increases \u003c=10% auto-execute\n\nCRO HANDOFF CHAIN (when CPL issue traced to LP/quality):\nCRO Specialist -\u003e UI/UX Designer -\u003e Developer -\u003e pixel verification in Events Manager\n(both Meta pixels observed + UTM passthrough confirmed) -\u003e LP sign-off\n\nAnalyze CPL data for ${ch}. Current channel CPL: $${cpl} USD.\nFind root cause and recommend fixes. Do NOT recommend pausing without checking 14-day window.\nOutput JSON: {\"root_cause\":str,\"worst_campaigns\":[{\"campaign_name\":str,\"cpl\":num,\"cpql\":num,\"recommendation\":str}],\"channel_recommendation\":str,\"asana_title\":str,\"requires_cro_handoff\":bool}`,\n  messages:[{role:\u0027user\u0027,content:`Channel: ${ch}\\nCurrent CPL: $${cpl} USD\\n\\nCampaign breakdown (CPL \u003e $38 USD):\\n${JSON.stringify(worst,null,2)}`}]\n}}];"
                                     }
                  },
                  {
                      "id":  "0c820cc4-9892-52b3-80dd-a3c783c3610c",
                      "name":  "Claude - CPL Analyst",
                      "type":  "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
